I gave it all I had, but these Hella Hot Outstanding Puffs just lit me up and my guy @lewishowes made sure I got cooled off with the quickness. S/O to @javalemcgee for all the great work he’s doing with his charity @juglifewater. 

I challenge @chriswharder, @edmylett & @mhiggins to the #HellaHotChallenge, a partnership between @outstandingfoods and @juglifewater to help raise awareness and encourage donations to bring clean drinking water to communities that need it most around the world. @outstandingfoods is matching all donations up to $10k 

Here's how you can participate:
1. Grab a friend, a cup of water and your Hella Hot Outstanding Puffs 🔥
2. Set up your camera and give your friend the cup of water 🚰
3. As soon as the 30 second timer begins, your friend becomes the judge. Hit go and start snacking, but keep that poker face! 😐
4. The second you crack, they get to throw the cup of water in your face… but, if you can last the full 30 seconds — snag that cup and throw the water on them 💦
5. When time is up (and one of you is wet), tell us the three or more people you’re challenging! 🏆
6. Post the video to your Instagram feed and/or TikTok and use the hashtag #HellaHotChallenge and tag both @outstandingfoods and @juglifewater as well as the 3+ others you challenged.

To learn more about the challenge hit the link in my bio and get involved 🙌🙌

Let’s keep pushing this mental health conversation. I challenge @lewishowes to #saysomething

node.text: Create, automate and optimize your way to more capacity and energy to live a fulfilling extraordinary life. That sentence really exemplifies what I have grown into over the last five years. I had the honor of being on @lewishowes podcast School of Greatness for the second time recently. Five years to the day we recorded the first podcast together in 2016. Lewis has since become a great friend and partner in both @get_mindright and @outstandingfoods. I laid out my vision for my life and work to him back 2016 and on this episode we get to recap what has happened and how I have evolved towards that vision. Super thankful for Lewis as a friend and love that we get to use the amazing platform he created to share the journey and lessons learned in my quest for extraordinary life. Can’t wait for the 10 year!

node.text: 🚨New Venture Alert🚨Proud to announce @jolieskinco as the newest addition to the @dyrdekmachine portfolio of brands. In this week’s episode of #BuildWithRob, I sit down with my newest Do-Or-Dier partner @ryanbbabenzien! We discuss our “shotgun venture creation wedding”, becoming partners in Jolie, as well as how important clean water is to our overall well being. One of the benefits of having a highly optimized process and a lot of experience is your heightened intuition. Ryan’s experience and vision for Jolie made this an easy deal to fast track. If you are curious what contaminants may be lurking in your water, go to www.jolieskinco.com and pop in your zip code for a free water report. If your hair and skin are feeling all sketchy, it’s most likely that your water is to blame!🚿🚿🚿🚿🚿 #manufacturingamazing

node.text: Special Guest Alert on the latest episode of #BuildWithRob. My man @lewishowes, who is not only a world renowned author and host of one of the biggest podcasts in the world, but is also a partner in two @dyrdekmachine portfolio companies — @get_mindright and @outstandingfoods. Lewis introduced me the the great @billglaser, CEO and Founder of Outstanding Foods. This episode we talk through our journey of connecting and the current issue of rebranding Take Out Puffs to Outstanding Puffs. As you grow a company you are faced with countless unexpected challenges and this rebrand is a perfect example. A ton of great lessons and insights in this episode from two of the best.

node.text: Happy Birthday to the Worlds Greatest Grandpa @genedyrdek1940

The truth about failure is it always hurts. There are no better lessons than those learned through watching a company struggle then ultimately go under. The latest episode of Build With Rob is the story of the @dyrdekmachine first loss since launching in 2016 . My man @dkozko is a real deal Do-Or-Dier entrepreneur but the market and customer adoption turned on him. We created an amazing venture @ultracastlive but we were not able to make it through the valley of death. Companies don’t work for a lot different reasons but there is no doubt we had an advantage in the motorsports market but chose to think broader and paid the ultimate price. When you play the game at this scale it is inevitable that you take a loss but it always sucks.

node.text: The Do-Or-Dier symbol represents who I am as a person, the people I surround myself with, and the entrepreneurs I Manufacture Amazing companies with @dyrdekmachine. It’s a mindset — a combination of relentless work ethic and an unwavering self-belief to create your own destiny. Do-Or-Diers are passionately compelled, relentlessly consistent, profoundly grounded, magnetically inspiring, perpetually optimizing, and honestly brilliant. Do-Or-Diers are a rare breed and I made these hats exclusively for the chosen few. Are you a Do-Or-Dier?

node.text: We had an amazing family adventure this week in beautiful Orlando, Florida. After her birthday @bryianadyrdek qualified to compete for the World’s Perfect Woman title. She won the title of World’s Perfect Miss when we were dating many years ago, so she had to wait till she turned 30 to be able to compete for another title. We brought the family out including @patdyr, @genedyrdek1940, and @secabrown to cheer her on. It was so much fun for us to watch her get back in the game she loves so much. So proud of her. In my opinion she won this title easy, but the judges did not seem to think so… maybe I’m biased, but don’t forget I judged Miss Universe back in 2014. Truth is she was, is, and will always be, World’s Perfect Woman to us.
